The advisory working group on Artificial Intelligence was appointed by the Minister of Education and Sciences of the Republic of Poland. This group includes members from various sectors: state (Ministry of Education and Sciences), commercial (Microsoft, Google), research (Institute for Educational Research, IBE), and educational organisations. This is a second guide in a series aimed at teachers, focusing on the integration of Artificial Intelligence in educational settings. This guide has been disseminated across Polish educational institutions at all levels through a state-managed digital educational platform.

